Certainly! Here's a poem in LaTeX format using alliteration with the word "banana":

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{poemscol}
\begin{document}

\begin{poem}
\poemtitle{Banana Breeze}

\begin{stanza}
Beneath the bending boughs, bananas bloom,\\
Brightly basking, bathed in balmy air.\\
Breezes blow, bringing banana bliss.\\
\end{stanza}

\end{poem}

\end{document}
```

This poem captures the essence of bananas in a serene, natural setting, using alliteration to create a rhythmic flow. You can copy and paste this into a LaTeX editor to see the formatted poem.
